- "guiding lights" metaphorically refers to the researchers;
- "illuminates the mysteries" metaphorically refers to gathering data or measurements on a species;
- The phrase "vast expanse" metaphorically represents the geographical area or the location of the study.

The phrase "greatest variety of species" refers to the highest count of distinct species recorded by researchers at their respective locations. ;
The researchers and locations are identified by their first and last names, and location names, respectively. ;
The data is derived from the intersection of researchers, locations, and species recorded in the iris measurements dataset. ;

- "species in bloom" metaphorically refers to different types of Iris species;
- "places they call home" symbolizes the various locations where these measurements were taken;
- "whispers of their average sepal dimensions" refers to the average sepal length and width calculated for each species at each location.

sql:
SELECT species_name, common_name
FROM iris_species
WHERE species_id = 0;

SELECT DISTINCT location_name 
FROM locations 
WHERE location_id IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT location_id 
    FROM iris_measurements
);

SELECT location_name
FROM locations
WHERE location_id IN (SELECT location_id FROM iris_measurements);

SELECT sepal_length
FROM iris_measurements
WHERE sepal_length < (SELECT AVG(sepal_length) FROM iris_measurements);
